TASTING EVENT

410
00:38:50.245 --> 00:38:51.204 line:80%
I'll try it.

411
00:39:06.261 --> 00:39:07.179 line:80%
What the hell?

412
00:39:08.972 --> 00:39:11.725 line:80%
It's so good. I think it'll be a hit.

413
00:39:14.561 --> 00:39:16.146 line:80%
This is our new product,

414
00:39:16.229 --> 00:39:19.441 line:80%
so try and make people
taste all three products.

415
00:39:19.524 --> 00:39:20.901 line:80%
-Okay?
-Okay!

416
00:39:20.984 --> 00:39:22.110 line:80%
Also...

417
00:39:33.330 --> 00:39:35.123 line:80%
I'll get the allergy sign.

418
00:39:43.757 --> 00:39:46.885 line:80%
Let's do two groups.
Those who shop after work

419
00:39:46.968 --> 00:39:48.053 line:80%
and housewives.

420
00:39:48.136 --> 00:39:50.180 line:80%
We have to check preference too. So...

421
00:39:50.263 --> 00:39:51.389 line:80%
I need to go pee.

422
00:39:52.432 --> 00:39:53.558 line:80%
Mr. Park!

423
00:39:53.642 --> 00:39:55.310 line:80%
Why haven't you started?

424
00:40:10.200 --> 00:40:11.326 line:80%
What are you doing?

425
00:40:13.286 --> 00:40:14.579 line:80%
Can you check this?

426
00:40:15.205 --> 00:40:16.206 line:80%
Yeah, sure.

427
00:40:24.840 --> 00:40:25.841 line:80%
What the...

428
00:40:27.300 --> 00:40:28.301 line:80%
What is this?

429
00:40:32.055 --> 00:40:33.557 line:80%
What do you think?

430
00:40:34.808 --> 00:40:35.809 line:80%
What?

431
00:40:37.853 --> 00:40:40.647 line:80%
We'll start the brief on Chef's Table,

432
00:40:40.730 --> 00:40:43.400 line:80%
the meal kit project
set to launch next year.

433
00:40:44.359 --> 00:40:46.403 line:80%
CHEF AND MENU INTRODUCTION

434
00:40:46.486 --> 00:40:48.321 line:80%
The winner of
One Dinner,

435
00:40:48.405 --> 00:40:51.366 line:80%
Lee Gwang-min's chicken dish
will be the pilot product.

436
00:40:51.449 --> 00:40:56.163 line:80%
Production will begin in the 1st quarter,
and it'll launch in the 2nd quarter.

437
00:40:56.997 --> 00:40:59.541 line:80%
Then we have Daniel Kim,
a traditional chef.

438
00:41:00.167 --> 00:41:04.838 line:80%
Along with Park Ji-ho who's popular
with those in their 20s and 30s...

439
00:41:10.886 --> 00:41:11.887 line:80%
Sir!

440
00:41:14.222 --> 00:41:15.557 line:80%
Well...

441
00:41:15.640 --> 00:41:20.353 line:80%
Thank you for trusting
and letting me take over this project.

442
00:41:24.232 --> 00:41:26.026 line:80%
Sure, you didn't trust me.

443
00:41:26.651 --> 00:41:31.156 line:80%
You just had no other choice
given the circumstances.

444
00:41:31.239 --> 00:41:36.745 line:80%
I'm sure that's why you suggested it.
Still, I was very thankful...

445
00:41:36.828 --> 00:41:38.788 line:80%
I just wanted to thank you...

446
00:41:44.502 --> 00:41:45.962 line:80%
That's not why.

447
00:41:46.046 --> 00:41:48.965 line:80%
I thought you would be capable
of doing it.

448
00:41:50.008 --> 00:41:50.842 line:80%
Pardon?

449
00:41:51.468 --> 00:41:53.011 line:80%
And finish your sentences.

450
00:41:53.803 --> 00:41:57.682 line:80%
Don't trail off whenever you speak.

451
00:41:57.766 --> 00:42:01.102 line:80%
Just say, "Thank you."

452
00:42:03.021 --> 00:42:04.481 line:80%
Yes, sir.

453
00:42:05.232 --> 00:42:09.653 line:80%
And when you get both good and bad
feedback, remember the good one too.

454
00:42:11.071 --> 00:42:12.113 line:80%
Pardon?

455
00:42:12.197 --> 00:42:15.784 line:80%
I said you would be capable of doing it.

456
00:42:17.410 --> 00:42:18.536 line:80%
Right.

457
00:42:18.620 --> 00:42:19.996 line:80%
Thank you.

458
00:42:29.172 --> 00:42:30.006 line:80%
Well, then.

459
00:42:40.308 --> 00:42:42.769 line:80%
